<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
When the report is authored by a government agency, include the name of the government followed by a comma then the name of the agency and any relevant page number(s) within parentheses immediately after the cited material. In a parenthetical citation, abbreviate terms that are commonly abbreviated, such as department (Dept.).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was shown in the report (Australian Government, Dept. of Health and Ageing).
</blockquote>
<br><br>
Or include the authors in your sentence, and any relevant page number(s) in parentheses.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The Australian Government, Department of Health and Ageing reported that&hellip; (11).
</blockquote>
<br><br>
When the author is referred to more than once in the same paragraph only the page number is needed for subsequent citations, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (Australian Government, Dept. of Health and Ageing 10-11). In addition &hellip;was a common feature (11).
</blockquote>
